                "byte_start": 105472,
                "byte_stop": 802523,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 7.862,
                        "byte_start": 105472,
                        "byte_stop": 136923,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.862,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 136923,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has our opinion in this morning in case 12-462, Northwest Incorporated v. Ginsberg."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.862,
                        "stop": 174.288,
                        "byte_start": 136923,
                        "byte_stop": 802523,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.862,
                                "stop": 20.174,
                                "byte_start": 136923,
                                "byte_stop": 186243,
                                "text": "This case presents the question whether the preemption provision of the Airline Deregulation Act of 1978 reaches the claim for breach of the implied covenant of good faith and fair dealing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.174,
                                "stop": 40.617,
                                "byte_start": 186243,
                                "byte_stop": 267954,
                                "text": "The respondent in this case was a participant in the Northwest Airlines frequent flyer program, and after taking a great many, Northwest flights and achieving a highest membership status, he was informed by Northwest that his membership was being terminated due to abuse of the program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.617,
                                "stop": 53.385,
                                "byte_start": 267954,
                                "byte_stop": 319049,
                                "text": "In taking the step, Northwest apparently relied on a provision in the frequent flyer agreement that gave Northwest sole discretion to determine whether a participant had abused the program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.385,
                                "stop": 68.18,
                                "byte_start": 319049,
                                "byte_stop": 378295,
                                "text": "Respondent then filed this action on behalf of himself and a class of similarly situated participants and he asserted claims for, among other things, breach of contract and breach of the covenant of good faith and fair dealing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.18,
                                "stop": 77.794,
                                "byte_start": 378295,
                                "byte_stop": 416747,
                                "text": "The District Court dismissed the breach of contract claim on the ground to not add issue before us and petitioner declined to appeal that decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.794,
                                "stop": 85.584,
                                "byte_start": 416747,
                                "byte_stop": 447885,
                                "text": "The District Court dismissed the breach of covenant claim holding that it was pre-empted by the Airline Deregulation Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.584,
                                "stop": 90.997,
                                "byte_start": 447885,
                                "byte_stop": 469514,
                                "text": "The respondent appealed that decision, the Ninth Circuit reversed and we granted certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.997,
                                "stop": 93.067,
                                "byte_start": 469514,
                                "byte_stop": 477769,
                                "text": "We addressed three issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.067,
                                "stop": 101.685,
                                "byte_start": 477769,
                                "byte_stop": 512251,
                                "text": "First, we reject respondent\u0027s argument that the Airline Deregulation Act preemption provision is limited to state statutes and regulations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.685,
                                "stop": 105.101,
                                "byte_start": 512251,
                                "byte_stop": 525939,
                                "text": "We hold that it also reaches common law rules."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.101,
                                "stop": 116.801,
                                "byte_start": 525939,
                                "byte_stop": 572750,
                                "text": "Second, we conclude that respondent\u0027s claim falls within the terms of the preemption provision which applies to claims that relate to rates, routes or services."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.801,
                                "stop": 138.885,
                                "byte_start": 572750,
                                "byte_stop": 661044,
                                "text": "The breach of contract claim qualifies because -- breach of covenant claim qualifies because the frequent flyer program awards mileage credits that can be used to reduce or eliminate the price of a ticket, so that concerns rates or to secure a service upgrade which obviously involves a service."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.885,
                                "stop": 163.689,
                                "byte_start": 661044,
                                "byte_stop": 760310,
                                "text": "Finally, we hold that under our interpretation of the preemption provision in the 1995 decision in American Airlines v. Wolens, a breach of covenant claim under the law of the relevant jurisdiction in this case, Minnesota is a state imposed obligation and not an obligation voluntarily undertaken by the parties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.689,
                                "stop": 171.883,
                                "byte_start": 760310,
                                "byte_stop": 793015,
                                "text": "For this -- for these reasons, we reverse the decision of the Ninth Circuit and remand for further proceedings consistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.883,
                                "stop": 174.288,
                                "byte_start": 793015,
                                "byte_stop": 802523,
                                "text": "Our decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
